"Aldehyde dehydrogenase","Dopamine beta-hydroxylase","Phenylethanolamine N-methyltransferase"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECatechol-O-methyltransferase (COMT)\u003C/strong\u003E converts adrenaline to metanephrine by methylating the 3-hydroxyl group on the catechol ring. This reaction produces metanephrine, which can be measured in urine to diagnose conditions of excess catecholamine production like pheochromocytoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other enzymes have different roles in catecholamine metabolism:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMonoamine oxidase (MAO)\u003C/strong\u003E converts adrenaline to 3,4-dihydroxymandelic acid through oxidative deamination\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAldehyde dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E converts 3,4-dihydroxyphenylglycolaldehyde to 3,4-dihydroxymandelic acid\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDopamine beta-hydroxylase\u003C/strong\u003E converts dopamine to noradrenaline\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhenylethanolamine N-methyltransferase\u003C/strong\u003E converts noradrenaline to adrenaline\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMeasuring urinary metanephrines is more reliable than measuring catecholamines directly because metanephrines are produced continuously, while catecholamine release can be episodic.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Elevated urinary metanephrines indicate increased catecholamine metabolism, which is a key diagnostic marker for pheochromocytoma","Catechol-O-methyltransferase (COMT) converts adrenaline to metanephrine, making metanephrine measurement useful for diagnosis"],"references":["Lotfi CFP, Kremer JL, Dos Santos Passaia B, Cavalcante IP. The human adrenal cortex: growth control and disorders. Clinics (Sao Paulo). 2018 Sep 6;73(suppl 1):e473s. doi: 10.6061/clinics/2018/e473s. PMID: 30208164; PMCID: PMC6113920","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA","Allen MJ, Sharma S. Physiology, Adrenocorticotropic Hormone (ACTH) [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK500031/Gaweska H, Fitzpatrick PF. Structures and Mechanism of the Monoamine Oxidase Family. Biomol Concepts. 2011 Oct 1;2(5):365-377. doi: 10.1515/BMC.2011.030. PMID: 22022344; PMCID: PMC3197729."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56488"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15637"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56488","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56488"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T18:50:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T18:51:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8328"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71018"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable f